02/05/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Deputy Secretary General Alessandro Minuto Rizzo met with Bulgarian Deputy Prime Minister Plamen Panayotov in Brussels on Friday (30 April). Panayotov reiterated Bulgaria's commitment to maintaining NATO's open door policy towards Macedonia, Croatia and Albania. He added that Bulgaria wants to see a clear commitment from NATO towards the Black Sea and Caucasian regions.
Also Friday, Bulgarian and Greek municipalities along the Arda River and its tributaries launched a joint project to make the river cleaner and to preserve ecological systems along its banks. The project would also establish an information network. (BTA, BTV, Mediapool - 30/04/04)
